obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE KING OF OU D H’S ESTATE VALIDATION ACT, 1917`
  line `A CT N O. XII OF 1917`
  line `[P ASSED BY THE I NDIAN L EGISLATIVE C OUNCIL.]`
  line `( Received the assent of the Governor General on the 21 st March, 1917. )`
  line `An Act to validate certain deeds of conveyance and a trust deed relating to certain properties of`
  line `His late Majest y, Wajid Ali Shah, King of Oudh, and for other purposes.`
  line `W HEREAS doubts have arisen as to the validity of three deeds of conveyance, all dated the 23 rd`
  line `November 1901, and a deed of declaration of trust of the same date, copies of which are set out in the`
  line `Schedule to this Act, and all of which deeds pu r port to relate to certain properties then or formerly of His`
  line `late Majesty, Wajid Ali Shah, King of Oudh (hereinafter, in this Act, called the late King), and in the case`
  line `of the said trust deed to declare the trusts of a certain Emambarra, mosque and burial ground, and for the`
  line `up - keep and maintenance thereof to constitute a certa in Endowment Fund hereinafter in this Act referred`
  line `to as the Sibtainabad Endowment Fund;`
  line `And Whereas by the said trust deed it was recite d or assumed inter alia that a share`
  line `amounting to rupees two hundred thousand in a certain Government Promissory Note No.`
  line `018878 for rupees five hundred thousand standing in the name of Malkai Kisshore and`
  line `deposited in the Government Treasury at Lucknow belonged to the estate of the late King, and`
  line `that the said share was to form a part of the Sibtainabad Endowment Fund, and the interest`
  line `thereon to be applied with the interest of certain other securities in the said trust deed referred`
  line `to for the up - keep and maintenance of the said Emambarra, mosque and burial ground;`
  line `And Whereas all interest from the 1 st of March 1901 to the 31 st of December 1913 payable`
  line `in respect of the said share of rupees two hundred thousand in the said Note has been paid and`
  line `credited to the Sibtainabad Endowm ent Fund along with the interest of the said other securities`
  line `and the said Emambarra, mosque and burial ground have been kept up and maintained thereout;`
  line `And Whereas it now appears that the said share of rupees two hundred thousand did not,`
  line `in fact, belong to the estate of the late King, and that on his death the interest thoreon was or`
  line `was intended to be payable to certain of the issue of the said Malkai Kisshore, and that the`
  line `in c lusion of the interest of the said share in the Sibtainabad Endowment Fund wa s due to a`
  line misapprehension;
  line `And Whereas there is now standing to the credit of the Sib tainabad Endowment Fund the`
  line `sum of rupees seventy - seven thousand eight hundred and fifty - six being the accumulated`
  line `balance after providing for the up - keep and maintenance of the said Emambarra, mosque and`
  line `burial ground;`
  line `And Whereas it is expedient that the said deeds of conveyance and the said trust deed and`
  line `all acts and things done thereunder should be validated, and that at the same time it should be`
  line `formally declared th at the said share of rupees two hundred thousand no longer forms a part of`
  line `the Sib t ainabad Endowment Fund, and that the interest thereon shall be made available as from`
  line `the 1 st of January 1914, for the persons who may hereafter be deemed entitled thereto u nder`
  line `the provisions hereinafter appearing;`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `And Whereas it is just and equitable that the said sum of rupees seventy - seven thousand`
  line `eight hundred and fifty - six should be released from the trusts of the said trust deed and should`
  line `also be made available for d istribution amongst the persons so entitled;`
  line `And W hereas it is also expedient to provide for the future management and distribution of`
  line `the said share of rupees two hundred thousand and of the interest accrued due since, the 1 st of`
  line `January 1914, and hereafter accruing due for time to time in respect thereof and also for the`
  line `distribution of any future surplus monies which may accrue to the said Sibtainabad Endowment`
  line `Fund after providing for the up - keep and maintenance of the said Emambarra mosque and`
  line `burial ground;`
  line `It is hereby enacted as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title. — This Act may be called the King of Oudh’s Estate Validation Act, 1917.`
  line `2. Validation of certain deed s. — N otwithstanding anything contained in any enactment`
  line `or any rule of law to the contrary, the three deeds of conveyance and the trust deed, copies of`
  line `which are set out in the Schedule, and all acts and things done under the said deeds are, save`
  line `as is hereinafter provided, validated and confirmed:`
  line `P rovided that, with effect from the 1 st of January 1914, the said trust deed shall be construed`
  line `as if no reference has been made therein to the share of rupees two hundred thousand of the`
  line `said Government Promissory Note, and as if the sum of rupees thirteen thousand six hundred`
  line `and thirty - four has been mentioned in the twelfth recital thereof instead of the sum of rupees`
  line `sixteen thousand, and the sum of rupees four hundred thousand instead of the sum of rupees`
  line `six hundred thousand, and with such further alterations and modification s as this construction`
  line `may require.`
  line `3. Payment of Rs. 77,856 from the Fund. — The sum of rupees seventy - seven thousand`
  line `eight hundred and fifty - six shall be released from the trusts of the said trust deed, and shall be`
  line `paid from the surplus monies of the said Sibtainabad Endowment Fund to such officer as the`
  line `Governor General in Counc il may appoint, and shall be distributed in the manner hereinafter`
  line provided.
  line `4. Distribution. — The sum referred to in section 3 and any further sums which the`
  line `Governor General in Council may at any time declare to be surplus monies of the Sibtainabad`
  line `Endowm ent Fund as he is hereby empowered to do, and all sums payable in respect of interest`
  line `on the said share of the said Government P romissory Note accrued due since the 1 st of January`
  line `1914, or hereafter to accrue due from time to time in respect thereof, are h ereby declared to be`
  line `pension s, and the said share of the said note is hereby declared to be a grant of money within`
  line `the meaning of the Pen sions Act, 1871 (XXIII of 1871), and that Act shall apply to such sums`
  line `as if they were pensions of the classes referre d to in sections 4 and 11 of the said Act and to`
  line `the said share as if it was a grant of the class referred to in section 4 of the said Act, subject,`
  line `however, to the following modifications, namely: —`
  line `( i ) any claim under section 5 of the said Act as applied shall be preferred to such officer as`
  line `the Local Government may authorize in this behalf;`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
