  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( ii ) the power of commutation conferred by section 10 of the said Act shall be exercisable`
  line `without the consent of the holder where the payment to be made is at a rate less than a rate of`
  line `rupee one per month; and`
  line `( iii ) the power to make rules conferred by sections 5 and 14 of the said Act shall extend to`
  line `a power to make rules prescribing the persons or classes of persons to whom, and the principles`
  line `on which, all distributions under this Act shall be made.`
  line `_______ __`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `THE SCHEDULE.`
  line ______
  line `Dated 23rd November, 1901.`
  line `H.C. EGGAR, E SQ.,`
  line `Agent under Act XIX of 1887`
  line to
  line `P RIN CE K UMAR K ADER M IRZA AND OTHERS.`
  line CONVEYANCE.
  line `H. C. EGGAR,`
  line `Solicitor to the Government of India.`
  line ________
  line `FIVE RUPEES.`
  line `ADMISSIBLE UNDER RULE 41.`
  line `Correctly stamped under the Indian Stamp Act,`
  line `Schedule I, No. 62.`
  line `T HIS I NDENTURE made the twenty - third day of November one thousand nine hundred and one`
  line `between Henry Cooper Eggar Solicitro to the Government of India and Agent under Act XIX of`
  line `1887 (hereinafter called the Agent) of the one part and Prince Kumar Kader Mirza Mahomed Abid`
  line `Ali of Kidderpore the eldest surviving son of His Majesty the late Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh`
  line `and Prince M irza Mahomed Jalall of 10 Shama Churn Dey’s Street Calcutta and Prince Mirza`
  line `Dilwar Jah of Garden Reach both sons of the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh of the other part`
  line `W ITNESSETH that by direction of the Governer General of India in Council and under t he`
  line `provisions of sub - section ( 1 ) of section I of Act XIX of 1887 of the Legislative Council of India`
  line `(being an Act to provide for the due administration of the estate of the said Wajid Ali Shah king`
  line `of Oudh) and the provisions of Act XIV of 1888 of the sam e Council the Agent doth hereby grant`
  line `convey and assign unto the said princes Kumar Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall and Mirza`
  line `Dilwar Jah their heirs executors administrators representatives and assigns without any warranty`
  line `of title all that piece or parc el of land belonging to the estate of the said Wajid Ali Shah King of`
  line `Oudh and Which has been used as a burial ground for the members of his family and is in the`
  line `Schedule hereto more particularly described together with all building and walls and all way,`
  line `paths, passages, trees, shrubs and underwoods, tanks, waters, watercourses, drains, rights,`
  line `casenients, appondages and appurtenances thereto belonging and therewith usually held used`
  line `occupied or enjoyed and all the estate right title and interest of the A gent of in and to the same`
  line `premises to H AVE A ND TO H OLD the said piece or parcel of land hereditaments and premises unto`
  line `and to the used of the said Princes Kumar Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall and Mirza Dilwar`
  line `Jah as joint tenants and not as tenants in common according to the nature and tenure thereof`
  line `respectively and the Agent enters into no covenant for title.`
  line `Fee paid`
  line Rs.
  line A..10
  line G.A..10
  line L..10
  line -----
  line 30
  line B.L.
  line CHANDRA,
  line Registrar.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `The Schedule above referred to.`
  line `All that piece or parcel of land situate on the north side of Circular Garden Reach Road at Garden Reach`
  line `in the Registration District of the twenty - four Pergunnahs Sub - District of Alipore and Thana Sonai Bazar`
  line `Containing an area of 19 bighas 8 cottahs and 1 chittack or thereabouts and which is surrounded on all sides`
  line `by walls and is bounded as follows that is to say on the north by the premises of the North - West Soap`
  line `Company Limited on the east by the premises and land of Baboo Durga Prosonn o Ghose on the S outh by`
  line `Circular Garden Reach Road and on the west by the premises of Prince Mirza Jam Jah Ali known as Futteh`
  line `Munzil or howsoever otherwise the said premises are or may be butted bounded called known or`
  line distinguished.
  line `IN WITHNESS whereof the said parties to these presents have hereunto set their respective hands and`
  line `seals the day and year first above written.`
  line `Signed sealed and`
  line `delivered by the above - H. C. EGGAR.`
  line `named Henry Cooper`
  line `Eggar in the presence of`
  line `ERNEST H. COWIE,`
  line `Solicitor, Calcutta.`
  line I
  line `247. 301.`
  line `Presented for Registration between the hours of 12 and 1p.m., on the 7 th day of February 1902, at the`
  line `Calcutta Registry Office, by E. H. Cowie, of Calcutta, by occupation Solicitor, executant, as Attorney for`
  line `H. C. Eggar under a Power - of - attorney authenti c ated by the Registrar of Calcutta on the 13 th July 1900 and`
  line `recorded as No. 193 for 1900.`
  line `ERNEST H. COWIE.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `7 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `Execution was admitted by the aforesaid attorney under the power cited above who is personally known`
  line `to me.`
  line `ERNEST H. COWIE.`
  line `BEHAR I LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `7 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `Registered in Book I.`
  line `Volume 25.`
  line `Pages 108 to 110.`
  line `Being No. 247.`
  line `For 1902.`
  line Seal.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
