obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line `Registrar, Calcutta.`
  line `18 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `Dated 23 rd November, 1901.`
  line `P RINCE KUMAR KADER MIRZA AND OTHERS`
  line `t o`
  line `P RINCES K UMAR K ADER M IRZA AND OTHERS.`
  line `C ONVEYANCE.`
  line `H. C. EGGAR,`
  line `Solicitor to the Government of Ind i a.`
  line ____________
  line `F IVE R UPEES.`
  line `ADMISSIBLE UNDER RULE 41.`
  line `Correctly stamped under the Indian Stamp Act,`
  line `Schedule I, No. 62.`
  line `THIS INDENTURE made the twenty - third day of November one thousand nine hundred and one`
  line `between Prince K umar Kader Mirza Mahomed Abid Ali of Kidderpore in the Suburbs of Calcutta the eldest`
  line `surviving son of His Majesty that late Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh and Prince Mirza Mahomed Jalall of`
  line `10 Shama Churn Dey’s Street Calcutta and Prince Mirza Dilwar Jah both sons of the said King of Oudh of`
  line `the one part and the said Princes Kumar Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall and Mirza Dilwar Jah and`
  line `Prince Mirza Mahomed Askari of Garden Reach in the Suburbs of Calcutta and Prince Mirza Ibrahim Ali`
  line `of Garden reac h both sons of the said King of Oudh (hereinafter called the said Mutwallis or Trustees) of`
  line `the other part. W HEREAS by Indenture of conveyance dated the twenty - third day of November on e`
  line `thousand nine hundred and one and made between Henry Cooper Eggar Soli citor to the Government of`
  line `India and Agent under Act XIX of 1887 (hereinafter referred to as the Agent) of the one part and the parties`
  line `hereto of the first part of the other part it was witnessed that by direction of the Governor General in Council`
  line `and und er the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ) of section I of Act XIX of 1887 (being an Act to provide for the`
  line `due administration of the estate of the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh) and the provisions of Act XIV`
  line `of 1888 of the same Council the Agent thereby granted conveyed and assigned unto the parties hereto of`
  line `the first part without warranty of title all that piece or parcel of land hereinafter more particularly described`
  line `and which formed part of the estate of the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh to hold unto the parties hereto`
  line `of the first part as joint tenants and not as tenants in common. A ND W HEREAS after the death of the said`
  line `Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh the said piece or parcel of land was by the desire of the members of his`
  line `family used as a burial ground for members of the family and the same was conveyed by the Agent by the`
  line `The Seal`
  line `of the`
  line Registrar
  line of
  line Calcutta.
  line `Fee paid`
  line Rs.
  line A..10
  line R..0.8
  line G.A..10
  line L..10
  line -----
  line 30.8
  line B.L.
  line CHANDRA,
  line Registrar.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `said Indenture of conveyance to the parties hereto of the first part as Trustees for and on behalf of the`
  line `members of the family as they do hereby adm it and acknowledge.`
  line `A ND W HEREAS it is desired by the members of the said family that the said burial ground shall be`
  line `main tained and kept up in conjunction with the Sibtainabad Emambarra at Garden Reach belonging to the`
  line `said family and that the said burial ground should accordingly be conveyed by the parties hereto of the first`
  line `part to the said Mutwallis or Trustees to the intent that they shall stand possessed of the same upon the`
  line `trusts declared of and concerning the same in and by a Wakfnamah or deed of t rust intended to be executed`
  line `by them of even date herewith.`
  line `A ND WHEREAS the parties hereto of the first part have accordingly agreed to convey the said burial`
  line `ground and the land whereon the same has been formed to the said Mutwallis or Trustees in manner`
  line `hereinafter appearing.`
  line `N OW THIS I NDENTURE W ITHNESSETH that in pursuance of the said desire and in consideration of`
  line `the premises they the said parties hereto of the first part do hereby without warranty of title grant convey`
  line `and assign unto the said Mutwallis or Trustees their Successors and assigns all that piece or parcel of land`
  line `in the Schedule hereto more particularly described and form ing and known as the Oudh Family burial`
  line `ground together with all buildings and walls and all ways, paths, passage s, trees, underwoods, drains,`
  line `waters, water - courses, rights, easements and appurtenances thereto belonging or therewith usually held`
  line `used occupied or enjoyed and all the estate right title and interest of the parties hereto of the first part to`
  line `have and to hold the said piece or parcel of land hereditaments and permises unto and to the use of the said`
  line `Mutwallis or Trustees as joint tenants and not as tenants in common according to the nature and tenure`
  line `thereof respectively upon the trusts declared of and co ncerning the same in and by the Wakfnamah or deed`
  line `of trust intended to be executed by them of even date herewith. And the parties hereto of the first part enter`
  line `into no covenants for title.`
  line `The Schedule above referred to.`
  line `All that piece or parcel of land s ituate at Garden Reach on the north side of the Circular Garden Reach`
  line `Road in the Registration District of the 24 - Pergunnahs Sub - District of Alipore and Thana of Sonai Bazar`
  line `containing an are a of 19 bigahs 8 cottahs and 1 chittack or thereabouts and surro unded on all sides by walls`
  line `and bounded on the north by the premises of the North - West Soap Company Limited, on the east by the`
  line `premises and land of Babu Durga Prosonno Ghose, on the south by Circular Garden Reach Road and on`
  line `the west by the premises of Pr ince Mirza Jam Jah Ali Known as Futteh Munzil or howsoever other wise`
  line `the said premises are or may be butted bounded called known or distinguished.`
  line `I N WITHNESS whereof the said parties to these presents have hereunto set their respective hands and`
  line `seals th e day and year first above written.`
  line `Signed sealed and KUMAR KADER`
  line `d elivered by the MEERZA.`
  line `above - named Prince`
  line `Kumar Kader Mirza in MOHMED ABID ALI.`
  line `the presence of —`
  line `ERNEST H. COWIE,`
  line `Solicitor, Calcutta.`
  line Seal.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
