  line 9
  line `Signed sealed and`
  line `delivered by the`
  line `above - named MIRZA MOHAMAD`
  line `Pri n ce Mirza Mahomed JALAL.`
  line `Jalall in the presence`
  line `of –`
  line `ERNEST H. COWIE.`
  line `Signed sealed and`
  line `delivered by the`
  line `above - named MIRZA DILAWAR`
  line `Prince Mirza JAH.`
  line `Dilwar Jah in t he`
  line `presence of —`
  line `ERNEST H. COWIE.`
  line `P.66 280 301 - 8.`
  line `Presented for registration between the hours of 12 and 1 p.m., on the 7 th day of February 1902, at the`
  line `Calcutta Registry Office, by Prince Kumar Kader Mirza Mohamed Abid Ali, son of His Majesty the late`
  line `Wajid Ali Shah, of Kidderpore, by o ccupation pensioner, executant.`
  line `KUMAR KADER MEERZA.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `7 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `Execution was admitted by the aforesaid executant who was identified by Ernest H. Cowie of Calcutta,`
  line `by occupation Solicitor.`
  line `KUMAR KADER MEERZA.`
  line `ERNEST BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line `H. COWIE. Registrar.`
  line `7 - 2 - 190 2.`
  line `Execution is this day admitted by Prince Mirza Mohamad Jalal, son of His Majesty the late Wajid Ali`
  line `Shah, of No. 10, Shama Churn Dey’s Street, Calcutta, pensioner, who is identified by Prasanna Kumar`
  line `Mookerjee, son of Gobind Chandra Mookerjee, of No. 5, Gokul Mitter’s Lane, Calcutta, Head Clerk,`
  line `Government Solicitor’s Office, Calcutta.`
  line `MIRZA MOHAMAD JALAL.`
  line `8 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `8 - 2 - 1902`
  line Seal.
  line Seal.
