obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `PROSONNO COOMAR MOOKERJEE,`
  line `Head Clerk, Government Solicitor’s Office.`
  line `Execution is this day admitted by Prince Mirza Dilawar Jah, son of His late Majesty Wajid Ali Shah,`
  line `of Garden Reach, 24 - Pergunnahs, pensioner, who is identified by Prasanna Kumar Mookerjee, son of`
  line `Gobindo Chandra Mookerjee, of No. 5, Gokul Mitter’s Lane, C alcutta, Head Clerk, Government Solicitor’s`
  line `Office, Calcutta.`
  line `MIRZA DIL A WAR JAH.`
  line `12 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `12 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `PROSONNO COOMAR MOOKERJEE,`
  line `Head Clerk, Government Solicitors’ Office.`
  line `Registered —`
  line `In Book I.`
  line `Volume 17.`
  line `Pages 64 to 68.`
  line `B eing No. 280.`
  line `For 1902.`
  line `BEHAR I LAL CHANDRA,`
  line `Registrar, Calcutta.`
  line `20 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `Dated 23rd November, 1901.`
  line `H.C. EGGAR, E SQ.,`
  line `Agent under Act XIX of 1887,`
  line `t o`
  line `P RINCE K UMAR K ADER M IRZA AND OTHERS.`
  line CONVEYANCE.
  line `H.C. EGGAR,`
  line `Solicitor to the Government of I ndia.`
