obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `STAMP RS. 5.`
  line `A DMISSIBLE UNDER R ULE 41.`
  line `Correctly stamped under the Indian Stamp Act,`
  line `Schedule I, No. 62.`
  line `THIS INDENTURE made the twenty - third day of November one thousand nine hundred`
  line `and one between Henry Cooper Eggar of Calcutta Solicitor to the Government of India`
  line `and Agent under Act XIX of 1887 (hereinafter called the Agent) of the one part and Prince`
  line `Kumar Kader Mirza Mahomed Abid Ali of Kidderpore the eldest surviving son of His Majesty the late`
  line `Wajid Ali Shah Kin g of Oudh and Prince Mirza Mahomed Jalal of 10 Shama Churn Dey’s Street Prince`
  line `Dilwar Jah of Garden Reach in the Suburbs of Calcutta Prince Mirza Mahomed Askari of Garden Reach`
  line `and Prince Mirza Ibrahim Ali of Garden Reach all sons of the said late King of Oudh of the other part.`
  line `WHEREAS His Majesty the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh in his life - time built and established upon`
  line `the plot of land hereinafter described an Emambarra or place of worship called and known as sibtainabad`
  line `Emambarra a description whe re of is firstly contained in the Schedule hereto and although so far as is known`
  line `no deed of wakf concerning the said Emambarra or building was ever executed or any specific dedication`
  line `of the said Emambarra or building as wakf property was ever made by the said Wajid Ali Shah King of`
  line `Oudh during his life - time the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh caused the said Emambarra of building to`
  line `be used as a place of public worship for Shiah Mahomedans up to the date of his death next hereinafter`
  line `recited A ND WHEREAS the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh died at Garden Reach in the Suburbs of`
  line `Calcutta on or about the twenty - first day of September one thousand eight hundred and eighty - seven and`
  line `was upon his death interred in the said Emambarra in accordance with his dyin g request and both before`
  line `and after his death certain members of his family were buried therein. A ND WHEREAS by Act XIV of 1888`
  line `of the Legislative Council of India after reciting Act XIX of 1887 of the same Council (being an Act to`
  line `provide for the administration by the Governor General in Council of the Estate of the said Wajid Ali Shah`
  line `King of Oudh) it was enacted that subject to the Control of the Governor General in Cou ncil the person for`
  line `the time being holding the office of Agent to the Governor General in Council for the affairs of the late`
  line `King of Oudh and for the purposes of Act XIX of 1887 might in his own name and in his name of office`
  line `dispose of any moveable or im moveable property of the said Wajid Ali Shah in as full and effectual a`
  line `manner as His Majesty could have disposed of it in his life - time A ND WHEREAS since the death of the said`
  line `Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh the said Emambarra has by the desire of the members of the late King’s`
  line `family continued to be used as a place of public worship and kept up out of the funds of the late King’s`
  line `Estate A ND WHEREAS by the desire of the members of the King’s family the small mosque or building`
  line `and piece or parcel of land with its approach way secondly in the schedule hereto described was after the`
  line `King’s death reserved from the sale of the properties belonging to his estate and set apart and demarcated`
  line `to the intent that the same might be used as a place of worship by Shiah Mah omedans and be kept up and`
  line `managed in conjunction with and as an appendage to the said Sibtainabad Emambarra. A ND WHEREAS it`
  line `is desired by the members of the said family that the said Emambarra and mosque should remain and be`
  line `places of public worship and b e a wakf according to Mahomedan Law under the charge of the parties of`
  line `the second part. A ND WHEREAS the parties of the second part have intimated their intention to execute a`
  line `wakfnamah or a Declaration of Trust of even date with these presents in order to carry out the wishes of the`
  line `late King and the members of the family. Now T HIS INDENTURE WITNESSETH that the Agent doth hereby`
  line `by the direction of the Governor General in Council grant convey and assign unto the said Princes Kumar`
  line `Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall, Mirza Dilwar Jah, Mirza Mahomed Askari and Mirza Ibrahim Ali the`
  line `parties of the second par t their heirs executors administrators representatives and assigns without any`
  line `warranty of title firstly all that building or Emambarra together with the piece or parcel of land on part`
  line `whereof the sa me is erected and built the Schedule hereto firstly more particularly described and which is`
  line `Fee paid.`
  line Rs.
  line `A.. 10`
  line `G.A.. 10`
  line `L.. 10`
  line `R.... 1`
  line -----
  line 31
  line -----
  line B.L.
  line CHANDRA,
  line Registrar.
