  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `Dated 23rd November, 1901.`
  line `P RINCE K UMAR K ADER M IRZA A BID A LI B AHADUR`
  line `P RINCE M IRZA M AHOMED J ALALL`
  line `P RINCE D ILWAR J AH M IRZA`
  line `P RINCE M IRZA M AHOMED A SKARI`
  line AND
  line `P RINCE I BRAHIM A LI.`
  line `DECLARATION OF TRUST.`
  line `H. C. EGGAR,`
  line `Solicitor to the Government of India.`
  line `S TAMP R S. 15.`
  line `A DMISSIBLE UNDER R ULE 41.`
  line `Correctly stamped under the Indian S tamp Act,`
  line `Schedule 1, No. 64.`
  line `TO ALL TO WHOM the presents shall come. We PRINCE KUMAR`
  line `KADER MIRZA ABID ALI BAHADUR of K idderpore in the Suburbs of Calcutta the eldest surviving son`
  line `of His Majesty the late Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh and PRINCE MIRZA MAHOMED JALALL of`
  line `S hama Churn Dey’s Street Calcutta PRINCE DILWAR JAH MIRZA of Garden Reach in the Suburbs of`
  line `Calcutta PRINCE MIRZA MAHOMED ASKARI of Garden Reach and PRINCE IBRAHIM ALI of`
  line `Garden Reach all sons of the said late King of Oudh.`
  line `S END G REETING.`
  line `1. W HEREAS His Majesty the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh in his life - ti me built and established`
  line `at Garden Reach in the Suburbs of Calcutta and Emambarra or place of worship called the Sibtainabad`
  line `Emambarra (a description whereof is contained in Part I of the First Schedule hereto) and although so far`
  line `as is known no Wakfnamah or deed of trust concerning the said Emambarra was ever executed or any`
  line `specific dedication of the said Ema mbarra as wakf property was ever made by the said King during his life -`
  line `time the said King caused the said Emambarra to be used as a place of public worship for Shiah`
  line `Mahomedans up to the date of h is death hereinafter recited and the said King was upon his death interred`
  line `in the said Emambarra in accordance with his dying request and both before and after his death certain`
  line `members of his family were in terred therein.`
  line `2. A ND WHEREAS the said Wajid Ali Shah King of O udh died at Garden Reach aforesaid on or about`
  line `the twenty - first day of September one thousand eight hundred and eighty - seven, being at the date of his`
  line `death possessed ( inter alia ) of the said Emambarra and the land on which the same stands but having made`
  line `no specific provision for the maintenance and up - keep of the said Emambarra after his death.`
  line `Fee paid`
  line Rs.
  line `F.. 1`
  line `G.A.. 1`
  line L..10
  line `R.. 4`
  line -----
  line 16
  line B.L.
  line CHANDRA,
  line Registrar.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `3. A ND WHEREAS by Act XIX of 1887 of the Legislative Council of India it was provided that the`
  line `Governor General in Council of India should have the exc l usive authority to act in the administration`
  line `of the property of whatever nature left by His late Majesty in regard to the settlement and satisfaction of`
  line `claim s against the estate of His late Majesty and might make disposition of the remaining property or the`
  line `proceeds thereof in such manner as he deemed fit amongst the family and dependants of the late King.`
  line `4. A ND WHEREAS by Act XIV of 1888 of the same Council after reciting Act XIX of 1887 it was`
  line `enacted that subject to the Control of the Governor General of India in Council, the person for the time`
  line `being holding the office of the Agent to the Governor General in Council for the affairs of the late King of`
  line `Oudh and for the purposes of Act XIX of 1887 might in his own name and by his name of office dispose`
  line `of any moveable or immoveable property of His late Majesty in as full and effectual a manner as His`
  line `Majesty could have disposed of it in his lifetime.`
  line `5. A ND W HEREAS since the death of the said Wajid Ali Shah King of Oudh the said Emambarra has`
  line `by the desire of the members of his family continued to be used as a place of public worship and has been`
  line `kept up and maintained out of the funds of the late King’s estat e.`
  line `6. A ND WHEREAS by desire of the members of the late King’s family the small mosque or building`
  line `and piece or parcel of land with its approach way in Part II of the first Schedule hereto described was after`
  line `the King’s death reserved from the sale of the p roperties belonging to his estate and set apart and`
  line `demarcated to the intent that the same might be used as a place of worship by Shiah Mahomedans and be`
  line `kept up and managed in conjunction with and as an appendage to the said Sibtainabad Emambarra.`
  line `7. A ND WHEREAS after the death of the late King in as much as the space for interments at the said`
  line `Sibtainabad Emambarra was found to be limited it become necessary for the members of the King’s family`
  line `to establish a private burial ground in which the said int erments might take place and which might be`
  line `managed with the said Sibtainabad Emambara.`
  line `8. A ND WHEREAS in accordance with the wish of the surviving members of the King’s family as`
  line `expressed by Princes Kumar Kader Mirza and Sir Jehan Kader Mirza since decea sed, Prince Mirza`
  line `Mahomed Jogee (since deceased) and the said Prince Mirza Mahomed Jalall the leading m embers of the`
  line `family and the first members of the Committee appointed temporarily by the Governor General in Council`
  line `to manage the said Sibtainabad Emamb ara the piece or parcel of l and and premises in Part III of the first`
  line `Schedule hereto more particularly described was reserved from the sale of the late King’s properties in`
  line `order that a burial ground might be established therein and a burial ground was fo rmed out of the said piece`
  line `or parcel of land and several members of the late King’s family have been interred therein.`
  line `9. A ND WHEREAS by an Indenture of Conveyance dated that twenty - third day of November one`
  line `thousand nine hundred and one the said piece or parcel of land forming the said burial ground was by the`
  line `direction of the Governor General in Council conveyed by Henry Cooper Eggar E squire Solicitor to the`
  line `Government of India and Agent to the Governor General in Council for the affairs of the late King of Oudh`
  line `and for the purposes of Act XIX of 1887 to us Princes Kumar Kader Mirza Muhammad Jalall and Prince`
  line `Dilwar Jah without warranty of title to hold unto us our exe cutors administrators and assigns as joint tenants`
  line `and not as tenants in common it being intended that we should subsequently convey the said premises to`
  line `Mutwallis or Trustees to be appointed by the Government of India to manage the said Emambarra and`
  line `burial ground.`
  line `10. A ND WHEREAS the affairs of the said King’s estate are about to be wound up finally and it is`
  line `necessary to make permanent provision for the endowment of the said Emambarra and mosque and burial`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-16
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Page 16`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `ground and the up - keep and maintenance thereof on a reasonable and proper footing consistent with the`
  line `status of the family and having reg ard to the fact that the said Emambarra contains the tomb of His late`
  line `Majesty and that other members of his family are interred therein.`
  line `11. A ND WHEREAS the Governor General in Council has decided with the consent and approbation of`
  line `the family of the late King that a sum shall be set aside out of the assets of the late King’s estate to purchase`
  line `Government securities sufficient with rupees two hundred thousand the share belonging to the estate of the`
  line `late King of Oudh of and in Government Promissory Note No. 018878 for rupees five hundred thousand`
  line `standing in the name of malkai Kissore and deposited in the Lucknow Treasury to provide the annual`
  line `income required for the up - keep of the said Emambarra mosque and burial ground and to form an`
  line `endowment for the said Emambarra mosque and burial ground out of which repairs and extra expenses not`
  line `met out of the usual yearly budget of expenditure may be met and satisfied and that the management of the`
  line `said Emambarra mosque and burial ground shall be entrusted to a body o f mutwallis or Trustees who shall`
  line `form the managing committee subject to the supervision and control of the Superintendent of Political`
  line `Pensions or such other officer as the Government of India may from time`
  line `to time appoint and subject to the observance of certain rules and regulations prescribed by t he Governor`
  line `General in Council and set fourth in the second and third Schedules hereto.`
  line `12. A ND WHEREAS the Governor General in Council has decided that the sum of rupees sixteen`
  line `thousand per annum is an ample provision for the proper up - keep and maintenan ce of the said Emambarra`
  line `mosque and burial ground and that a sum of rupees six hundred thousand in all is sufficient to set aside to`
  line `provide such yearly sum and form the Endowment Fund and the Government securities of the parvalue of`
  line `rupees four hundred t housand of which the particulars are given in Part I of the fourth Schedule hereto have`
  line `been purchased and set apart out of the assets of the estate of the late King and endorsed to and placed with`
  line `the Comptroller General to form with the said share of Gov ernment Promissory Note No. 018878 for rupees`
  line `five hundred thousand the fund for the endowment of the said Emambarra mosque and burial ground the`
  line `interest on such Government securities and on the said share of Government Promissory Note No. 018878`
  line `for rupe es five hundred thousand which will be drawn by the Comptroller General from he Lucknow`
  line `Treasury to be applied in paying to the Mutwallis or Trustees to be appointment by these presents the sum`
  line `of rupees sixteen thousand for the up - keep and maintenance of the said Emambarra mosque and burial`
  line `ground or such less sum as may in the discretion of the Superintendent of Political Pensions be found`
  line `necessary and which they are to apply in accordance with the terms of these presents and the balance of`
  line `such interes t to b e credited to the endowment fund.`
  line `13. A ND WHEREAS it is possible that further sums or securities may hereafter be added to the said`
  line `fund by order of the Governor General in Council and it is intended that any such sums or securities shall`
  line `after publication of an order to that effect in the Gazette of India be dealt with as if they had formed part of`
  line `the original endowment above recited.`
  line `14. A ND WHEREAS we the said Princes Kumar Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall, Mirza Dilwar`
  line `Jah, Mirza Mahomed As kari and Ibrahim Ali have been nominated and appointed by the Governor General`
  line `in Council to be the first Mutwallis or Trustees and members of the Managing Committee of the said`
  line `Emambarra mosque and burial ground and by Indenture of even date herewith the said Emambarra and the`
  line `land on which it stands (which are more particularly described in Part I of the f irst Schedule hereto) and the`
  line `said mosque and the land on which it stands it stands and the app roach way (which are more particularly`
  line `described in Part II of the first Schedule hereto) have been conveyed and assured by the said Henry Cooper`
  line `Eggar Esq. Solicitor to the Government of India and Agent to the Governor General in Council for the`
  line `affairs o f the late King of Oudh and for the purposes of Act XIX of 1887 to us the said Princes Kumar`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-17
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Page 17`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  sourcePage 17
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall, Mirza Dilwar Jah, Mirza Mahomed Askari and Ibrahim Ali without`
  line `warranty of title to be held by us as joint tenants and not as te nants in common and by another Indenture of`
  line `Conveyance of even date herewith the said burial ground and premises described in Part III of the said first`
  line `Schedule hereto have been conveyed by us the said Princes Kumar Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall`
  line `and Dilwar Jah to us the said Princes Kumar Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall, Mirza Dilawar Jah,`
  line `Mirza Mahomed Askari and Ibrahim Ali without warranty of title to be held upon the trusts declared of and`
  line `concerning the same by an Indenture of Wakfnamah or deed of trust of even date therewith being these`
  line `presents. Now these presents witness that we the said Princes Kumar Kader Mirza, Mirza Mahomed Jalall,`
  line `Mirza Dilwar Jah, Mirza Mahomed Askari and Ibrahim Ali do hereby declare that we and our successors`
  line `in the o ffice of Mutwallis or Trustees will henceforth stand possessed of the said Emambarra mosque and`
  line `burial ground and the appurtenances thereto respectively belonging and of the income and interest from the`
  line `said Endowment fund that may come into our hands and of all other moneys that may come into our hands`
  line `as Mutwallis or Trustees of the said Emambarra and burial Ground upon the trusts hereinafter declared and`
  line `contained of and concerning the same respectively that is to say upon trust that the said Emambarra a nd`
  line `mosque with the appurtenances shall remain and be wakf property in the hands of us the said Mutwallis`
  line `and our successors in that office according to Shiah Mahomedan Law and that we and our successor shall`
  line `permit the same to be used as places of public w orship for Shiah Mahomedans and will conduct and manage`
  line `the affairs thereof in accordance with the rules and regulations set forth in the second Schedule hereto and`
  line `under the s upervision of the Superintendent of Political Pensions or such other officer of Government as`
  line `the Governor General in Council may from time to time appoint in that behalf and upon trust that the said`
  line `burial ground shall remain and be wakf property in the hands of us the said Mutwallis and our successors`
  line `in that office according to Shi ah Mahomedan Law and shall be used as a place of interment for members`
  line `of the late King’s family and their descendants in accordance with the rules and regulations set forth in the`
  line `third Schedule hereto and under the supervision of the said Superintendent of Political Pensions or other`
  line `officer as aforesaid and as regards the income and interest of the said Endowment Fund and all other moneys`
  line `that may come to our hands as Mutwallis or Trustees of the said Emambarra mosque and burial ground`
  line `upon trust to appl y the same in the due and proper up - keep and maintenance of the said Emambarra mosque`
  line `and burial ground and the performance and observance of the Mohurrum and other necessary and proper`
  line `ceremonies or observances at the said Emambarra in the same manner as far as may be and circumstances`
  line `will permit as the said Emambarra mosque and burial ground have been kept up and maintained and the`
  line `said Mohurrum and other ceremonies and observances have been performed and observed under the`
  line `supervision and direction of t he Governor General in Council since the death of the said Wajid Ali Shah`
  line `King of Oudh and that the scale of expenditure shall be regulated as far as may be and circumstances may`
  line `permit by the scale set forth in Part II of the fourth Schedule hereto and up on which scale the said sum of`
  line `rupees sixteen thousand per annum has been arrived at as the proper amount to be expended in the up - keep`
  line `and carrying on of the said Emambarra Mosque and burial ground and we do hereby declare and agree that`
  line `the provisions of the Mahomedan Law as to the appointment and removal of Mutwallis for reasons admitted`
  line `of recogni s ed by that Law shall be expressly applicable to the said Emambarra mosque a n d burial ground`
  line `the right of removing any Mutwallis and appointing new Mutwallis in place of those dying or removed`
  line `being vested in the Governor General of India in Council and that we and our successors in the office of`
  line `Mutwallis shall abide by the rules and regulations contained in the said second and third Schedules hereto`
  line `and that we will keep and render to the Superintendent of Political Pensions or to any other officer`
  line `nominated by the Governor General in Council true and proper accounts of all sums of money that may`
  line `pass through our hands.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
