obj_root_law_sections_18:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-18
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Page 18`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line _______
  line `The first Schedule above refe rred to.`
  line `P ART I.`
  line `All that Emambarra or building together with the piece or parcel of land on which the same is erected`
  line `and build situate and being at Garden Reach on the south side of the Garden Reach Road in the Registration`
  line `District of the 24 - Pergunnahs Sub - district of Alipore and Thanna of Sonai Bazar Containing an area of 1`
  line `bigah 9 cottahs 7 chittacks or thereabouts and bounded on the north by Garden Reach Road on the south by`
  line `land belonging to the bhookoilash Raj Estate on the east partly by the premises of the late Nawab Yadyar`
  line `Mehal Sahiba and partly by a piece of land belonging to the Estate of the late Prince Mirza Mahomed Jogee`
  line `Bahadur and on the west by an old building said to be the property of one Rais Hyder and formerly known`
  line `as the house of the late Zulfikur - ud - Dowlah.`
  line `P ART II.`
  line `All that small mosque or building together with the piece or parcel of land whereon the same is erected`
  line `and built situate within the grounds of the premises known as the Shah Munzil belonging to the Estate of`
  line `the late Prince Sir Jehan Kader Mirza at Garden Reach in the Registration District Sub - district and Thana`
  line `aforesaid and bounded on the north by the court yard of the Shah Munzil on the south partly by the private`
  line `road lead ing fr o m the Shah Munzil to the Sulatan Bazar Road and partly by a tank on the east by Iron Gates`
  line `belonging to the Shah Munzil and on the west partly by the approach way leading to the mosque from the`
  line `road leading from Garden Reach Road down to the river a nd partly by the Shah Munzil premises together`
  line `with the last mentioned approach way or passage passing through an opening in the wall of the Shah Munzil`
  line `premises and leading on to the road running from Garden Reach Road to the river the length of such way`
  line `from the mosque being 72 feet.`
  line `PART III.`
  line `All that piece or parcel of land situate on the north side of Circular Garden Reach Road at Garden Reach`
  line `in the Registration District of the 24 Pergunnahs sub - district of Alipore and Thannah Sonai Bazar`
  line `containing a n area of 19 bighas 8 cottahs and one chittack or thereabouts and which is surrounded on all`
  line `sides by walls and is bounded as follows that is to say on the north by the premises of the North - West Soap`
  line `Company Limited on the east by the premises and land of Babu Durga Prosonno Ghose on the south by`
  line `C ircular Garden Reach Road and on the west by the premises of Prince Mirza Jam Jah Ali known as Futteh`
  line `Munzil or howsoever otherwise the said premises are or may be butted bounded called known or`
  line distinguished.
  line `__ _______`
  line `The second Schedule above referred to.`
  line `R ULES FOR THE GUIDANCE OF THE T RUSTEES OR M UTWALLIS.`
  line `1. Interest on the Government Promissory Notes for the time being representing the Endowment Funds`
  line `(including the share of the Note No. 018878 for Ɍ 5,00,000 in the Lucknow Treasury) shall be drawn as the`
  line `same accrues due by the Accountant General Bengal who shall credit the same to the “Sibtainabad`
  line `Emambarra Endowment Fund” for which a personal ledger account will be opened in the Bank of Benga l`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-19
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Page 19`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `in favour of the Superintendent of Political Pensions the account being charged with the amounts drawn by`
  line `the Superintendent on cheques upon the bank.`
  line `2. The Trustees shall every year draw up a budget estimate of the expenditure required for the`
  line `maintena nce of the Emam bara and burial ground which shall be submitted for the sanction of the`
  line `Superintendent of Political Pensions.`
  line `3. The Trustees shall appoint a Manager subject to the sanction of the Superintend ent of Political`
  line `Pensions who shall be empowered to submit requisition for ordinary and recurring expenditure to the`
  line `Superintendent of Political Pensions. If such bills are within the sanctioned estimates cheques shall be`
  line `drawn by the Superintendent of Political Pensions for the amount. Other bills shall be paid on the requisition`
  line `of the Trustees in meeting if the Superintendent shall approve of the expenditure proposed.`
  line `4. The Manager of the Emambarra shall also be in charge of the burial ground and the small mosque`
  line `above referred to.`
  line `5. The Manager may appoint and dismiss the servants of the Emambarra and burial ground subject to`
  line `the approval of the Trustees and the Superintendent of political Pensions. The Trustees may remove the`
  line `Manager in case of misconduct subject to the Superintendent ’s sanction.`
  line `6. Regular accounts of expenditure shall be prepared by the Manager once a month and shall be`
  line `submitted through the Trustees to the Superintendent of Political Pensions for his inspection.`
  line `7. The Manager should perform all religious ceremonies under the inst ructions of the Trustees. If there`
  line `should be a difference of opinion among the several Trustees the matter shall be decided by the majority.`
  line `The minority may however appeal to the Superintendent against any decision of the majority and until such`
  line `an appeal has been decided by the Superintendent he can suspend any action by a majority of the Trustees`
  line `which a minority of them have appealed against. When an even number of Trustees is present and they are`
  line `equally divided upon any point they should appeal to the Superintendent to decide on the matter in dispute.`
  line `8. The right of removing any Trustees on their conducting the affairs of the Emambarra in opposition`
  line `to the object of this Trust or on their violating any rules which may be in force at the time and of ap pointing`
  line `new Trustee in the place of those dying or removed shall be vested in the Superintendent of Political`
  line `Pensions subject to the approval of the Government of Bengal.`
  line `9. The Trustees shall hold meetings on c e a month. The proceedings of each meeting s hall be submitted`
  line `to the Superintendent of Political Pensions.`
  line `10. The details of expenditure for the proper up - keep of the Emambarra and the mosque shall be settled`
  line `by the Trustees with the sanction of the Superintendent of Political Pensions subject to t he approval of the`
  line `Government of Bengal.`
  line `11. The rules shall be liable to revision from time to time on the recommendation of the Trustees and`
  line `subject to the approval of the Superintendent of Political Pensions and the Government of Bengal.`
  line `12. A list of the Emambarra moveable shall be made by the Manager every year and submitted through`
  line `the Trustees to the Superintendent of Political Pensions.`
  line ________
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
