  title `Page 20`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `The third Schedule above referred to.`
  line `R ULES FOR THE MANAGEMENT OF THE BURIAL GROUND.`
  line `1. The following is a list of the members of the Oudh family who shall have the right to be interred in`
  line `the burial ground: —`
  line `( 1 ) The sons of the late King.`
  line `( 2 ) Daughters of the late King.`
  line `( 3 ) The grand and great grandchildren of the late King.`
  line `( 4 ) The Motahi wives of the late King who had recogni s ed issue by His Majesty.`
  line `( 5 ) The Nikah wives of the sons of the late King.`
  line `( 6 ) The two daughters of the late Prince Sir Jehan Kader and their children.`
  line `2. No. interment shall be made except in accordance with t he above rules and with the sanction of the`
  line Trustees.
  line `3. The minimum depth of a grave shall be eight feet.`
  line `4. The grave shall be filled in with earth and bricked over cement being put over the bricks and marble`
  line `slabs over the cement.`
  line `5. The burial ground shall be kept as clean as possible and the Superintendent of Political Pensions may`
  line `cause it to be inspected from time to time by a Mahomedan gentleman to be selected by the Trustees.`
  line `6. The details of expenditure for the maintenance of the burial ground s hall be settled by the Trustees`
  line `and the necessary funds shall be drawn by the Manager in the same way as in the case of the Emambarra.`
  line ________
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
