obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA.`
  line Registrar.
  line `7 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `Execution was admitted by the aforesaid executant who was identified by E.H. C owie, of Calcutta, by`
  line `occupation Solicitor.`
  line `KUMAR KADER MEERZA.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `7 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `ERNEST H. COWIE.`
  line `Execution was also admitted by Prince M.M. Askari, son of His Majesty the late Wajid Ali Shah, of`
  line `Garden Reach, Pensioner, who was Identified by M. Abbott of Calcutta, Solicitor.`
  line `M.M. ASKARI.`
  line `M. ABBOTT.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `7 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `Execution is this day admitted by Price Mirza Mahomed Jalal, son of His Majesty the late Wajid Ali`
  line `Shah of No. 10, Shama Charan Dey’s Street, Calcutta, Pensioner, who is identified by Prasanna Coomar`
  line `Mookerjee, son of Govind Chandra Mookerjee, of No. 5, Gokul Mitter’s Lane, Calcutta, Head Clerk,`
  line `Government Solicitor’s Office, Calcutta.`
  line `MIRZA M O HAMAD JALAL.`
  line `8 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA,`
  line Registrar.
  line `8 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `PROSONNO COOMAR MOOKERJEE,`
  line `Head Clerk, Government Solicitor’s Office.`
  line `Execution is this day admitted by Prince Mirza Dilawar Jah and Prince Ibrahim Ali Mirza, sons of His`
  line `late Majesty Wajid Ali Shah, both of Garden Reach, 24 - Pergunnahs, p ensioners, who are identified by`
  line `Prasanna Coomar Mookerj ee, son of Govind Chandra Mookerjee of No. 5, G o kul Mitter ’s Lane, Calcutta,`
  line `Head Clerk, Government Solicitor’s Office, Calcutta.`
  line `MIRZA DILAWAR JAH.`
  line `12 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `IBRAHIM ALI MEERZA.`
  line `12 - 2 - 1902.`
  line `BEHARI LAL CHANDRA.`
  line Registrar.
  line `12 - 2 - 1902.`
